<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1377">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.11/75.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Mexican
                                Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 149.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-05">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                            the receipt of your note of the 1st instant, from which the Department
                            is gratified to learn that your Government has appointed commissioners
                            at El Paso, Texas, and Douglas, Arizona, to attend to the damage claims
                            arising from the battles that occurred at Ciudad Juárez and Agua Prieta;
                            and in reply I beg to say that this Government earnestly hopes that this
                            matter will be settled with the least possible delay.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>